    "industrial_process_notes": "Not industrially polymerized -- biosynthesized as latex in Hevea brasiliensis (Para rubber tree) and harvested by tapping (bark incisions collected in cups). A skilled tapper processes several hundred trees daily; collected latex is coagulated (acid or ammoniation, developed c. 1920, to preserve colloidal state) into cup lump, tree lace, or technically-specified block rubber grades (SVR/TSR).",
